@DarthKithkin:


You have a [Fugitive Wizard](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fugitive Wizard) enchanted with [Freed from the Real](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Freed from the Real) and [Quicksilver Dagger](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Quicksilver Dagger).

If an opponent gains control of your creature with [Act of Treason](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Act of Treason), he can use the ability of the Dagger because it is "granted" to the creature ("Enchanted creature has..."). He can't use [Freed from the Real](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Freed from the Real) because its ability is not depending on control of the enchanted creature. You still control both auras though.
